The paper deals with the problem of channel sensing in molecular communication, which involves the estimation of the concentration of multiple types of ligands in a crowded channel. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) as it involves the estimation of information from noisy measurements. The proposed solution also involves the use of synthetic receptors and chemical reaction networks, which are related to neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of ligands as information carriers between nanomachines, which is related to molecular machines (cs.MM) and synthetic biology (cs.BIO).
